sentences: During the 1940s, Ventura played saxophone for the bands of Gene Krupa and Teddy Powell.
In 1945 he was named best tenor saxophonist by DownBeat magazine.
He was a sideman with Krupa through the 1960s, then worked in Las Vegas with comedian Jackie Gleason.
In 1992 he died of lung cancer.
